Title : Torvald Klaveness Group
Text : [[File:Klaveness Marine IMG 6349 sköyen.JPG|thumb|Headquarters at [[Skøyen]].]]

The '''Torvald Klaveness Group''' is a Norwegian [[shipping company]] founded in 1946. '''Klaveness Marine''' was demerged from it in 2011.

==History==
The company was founded by [[Torvald Faye Klaveness]] in 1946, who served as the company's president and chief executive officer until 1989. He was succeeded by his son Tom Erik Klaveness, who was later succeeded by another of Torvald's sons Trond Harald Klaveness in 2006.<ref name=nbl>{{cite encyclopedia|year=|title=Torvald Klaveness|encyclopedia=[[Norsk biografisk leksikon]]|first=Bård|last=Kolltveit|editor=[[Knut Helle|Helle, Knut]]|publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget|location=Oslo|url=http://nbl.snl.no/Torvald_Klaveness|language=Norwegian|accessdate=29 April 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://klaveness.com/company/history/|title=History|publisher=Torvald Klaveness Group|accessdate=29 April 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.klavenessmarine.com/Company/History2|title=History|publisher=Klaveness Marine|accessdate=29 April 2014}}</ref>

By the early 2000s the company owned a fleet of almost 150 [[bulk cargo]] vessels.<ref name=snl>{{cite encyclopedia|year=|title=Torvald Klaveness Gruppen|encyclopedia=[[Store norske leksikon]]|editor=|publisher=|location=|url=http://www.snl.no/Torvald_Klaveness_Gruppen|language=Norwegian|accessdate=29 April 2014}}</ref> In 2011 the two Klaveness brothers decided to demerge the holding and real estate division, forming '''Klaveness Marine''' with Tom Erik Klaveness as majority owner. Trond Harald Klaveness continued in the Torvald Klaveness Group which remained a shipping company, but now as president whereas Lasse Kristoffersen became the new chief executive.<ref>{{cite news|title=Delte broderlig|work=Dagens Næringsliv|date=13 September 2011|page=21|language=Norwegian|author=Sægrov, Bjørn}}</ref>

